  ### 3\. Display Important Words in Bold
  
  Use **bold** formatting to stress important ideas readers should pay extra attention to.
  
  For instance, this Knitandnote blog post uses bold formatting to emphasize key details for each knitting pattern.
  
  ![Bold text in Knitandnote blog post highlighted.](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/ad/74/ad74155c7b1bd9295d3a85ea73f7bb65/1424e1e7db84e9d4a237a1b1c648243f/AD_4nXezyPH25wb3S_DR2hfM9vVI2tMxO8MN5WMYlYSiHw0cEIbquL8K6JKwnQLFEzW3BbBXSujr4JpOBsg4I5W-t4pi0avzu9IudoH-S9jpu-YREqeYmoOwVQWm75YPnHTYRgnDzd93VVmybPaRPI-lRPM8rKZw.png)
  
  Bolded text looks thicker than unbolded text. So, it stands out on the page. And catches the reader’s eye.
  
  To bold your text, highlight it in your writing app or CMS. Then, click the bold icon:
  
  ![Bold text selected in Google docs and Bold format button highlighted.](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/29/e9/29e91a20a62d0ad89bafe27a060e71c8/bd0b00d568df88fef013d647a9ee5f2a/AD_4nXcTM652gE7xib8_Linfj3nGUaHm2K0ko0UmS8p0Ns8NXjDiFLZqUvNf8n34tt5cA0cxm_QowoQKV8r7Sd6_lkcGc6udHOLqNqLTEBexvZwghNVtD1zjB6bsjId-J-PpDaKEyI4zInwrqf6FqVNXXB2Oj25R.png)
  
  And don’t use underlines for emphasis. Because readers may mistake underlined text for links.
  
  ### 4\. Create Lists
  
  Lists are a series of points presented one after another. They help you:
  
  - Display multiple related points concisely
  - Present information in a sequential order
  - Add visual variety to your post
  
  List points have a symbol—known as a prefix character—in front of them to mark the start of each point.
  
  For example, the prefix character for the list above is a black circle (also known as a bullet).
  
  There are two types of lists:
  
  #### Ordered Lists
  
  Ordered lists display points in a specific order.
  
  Their prefix characters are typically numbers or letters. And they display their points in ascending order (like from one to 10) to tell readers the order in which they should read them.
  
  For example, if you’re sharing instructions, presenting them as an ordered list helps readers understand the sequence.
  
  Just like this numbered list of steps in Mnmlscholar’s blog post:
  
  ![Numbered list in blog post highlighted.](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/65/45/65452d422c537565b40e6b558735dc1b/b9852411c263790b933e377289b2ef83/AD_4nXehRCsJrtRlkd5IMtFzKrTobPB8R-GMu4Yvycaq-pIYpB-xjSE4IrsXkWVWNKBoilGRJtwfVTgnaBdhsng4dl-lbzkJ0NXAahdN1eRJjFuO7ODW2GHQdMb9sHiki3DjUOO8In7o9YvcGi1Yv4BtELt1wF-y.jpeg)
  
  Presenting information in ordered lists also helps readers keep track of their progress through the discussion.
  
  For instance, this very blog post provides seven formatting tips. We’re currently at the fourth tip. So, we’re just over halfway through.
  
  To create an ordered list, click the ordered list icon in your writing app or CMS. It looks like a numbered list:
  
  ![Numbered list button highlighted in Google docs editor toolbar.](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/c8/95/c89553ce42555da5e9308c06d9f6364d/000c47ccc327bc0c197be6bd9e397a8e/AD_4nXckUn51wArFaJkIHRb54yfiXxz3rmRHvHJppY2Dh5568PrIX1r4VJoRwrWwZIVPsBuUeJFQu6N4ITqCYH_-W4c-U3T3Joqh20KKLmBszWtlGLxjUGNd8AXRuMD0v0YkA1_ywXlh56fVq7jniCzQnUS_ak7S.png)
  
  A first numbered list point will appear. Type your text, and then hit “ **Enter**” or “ **return**” on your keyboard to add more points.
  
  Your writing app or CMS should also let you change your ordered list’s prefix character from numbers to letters (or vice versa).
  
  ![Numbered list dropdown options expanded and highlighted.](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/09/36/09360a0ddea55a254d057b77becaf71b/5f395d6663ecea1a21eb4ebc958eb62c/AD_4nXfJSXGCicsyBRgdYlvwPzQoYqT1TJJ2JiVuhST7HWDSbqwr0HmGj5tTmJfMaoY7CA1hWaC2kdPwc8HOuBxpR-AVmN8FjVFdX4MJqID2Tu2yY9wASfOrgBlGGSV4AXkldYKImCZ6Qm-PxHqH6EmD2QyU2g_6.png)
  
  #### Unordered Lists
  
  Unordered lists display points in no particular sequence. Their points also share the same prefix character, like a bullet or dash.
  
  This list on The Manual’s blog post is unordered:
  
  ![Unordered list in The Manual blog post.](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/22/8b/228b869450d36e229cdf49ab125024f9/8ef9763816fc0010563e7059f1d253ed/AD_4nXdMy2tPOAsbksB14xMndiQkg8vFPdRygVmj-hWa4VbRhPVdnXRcpvHsbnno_K80V9OLyVji1rcwhZ0PdxdyomidFGgoNZPlrY0nlEUOI9m_PCaC6ysCxwo4N4h8t5hXrgfeHtxZ495NyXWmeWjll6cGYQtJ.png)
  
  Present your points in an unordered list if each point has equal importance. And the order in which people read them doesn’t matter.
  
  To create an unordered list, click the unordered list icon in your writing app or CMS. It looks like a list with bullet points:
  
  ![Unordered list button in Google Docs toolbar highlighted.](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/2e/29/2e2991d64e7896cb040a260dd7fdd636/9785445da5dfc5d4e811f7a173802f86/AD_4nXeGogqUiOvWgDA-dEwWccFaL_iZdyNE8qeevJSmSEGnJpK857HRFLnrzBB_IF5CyaXt0AHM5g6Ghh76-wgLmsK1HbBgmDRZME7PXzYjOGk7P6eIb9mFnaNpjk_qp9-g6t901ppsYCXOLDHcSGkteEffN7Q.png)
  
  An unordered list point will appear. Type your text, and then add more points by pressing “ **Enter**” or “ **return**” on your keyboard.
  
  ### 5\. Insert Visuals
  
  Visuals depict concepts in a graphical format. And can help make complex ideas easier to understand.
  
  Visuals also add color and visual variety. Making your content more appealing.
  
  Some examples of visuals are:
  
  #### Images and Videos
  
  WikiHow uses text alongside static and animated images to explain the process of making a paper bag.
  
  If readers find the text instructions confusing, they can follow the image demonstrations instead.
  
  ![a screenshot from "wikiHow to Make a Paper Bag" animated image](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/f4/c4/f4c4bba1a9204d4bbe2fd3a30f45b774/e1fc6b94a1d7e284a4c46f1a218d2190/AD_4nXebAMrKoAcxTjHcJhwED7Inarep7UXPpwE75mv3ZpAUBhvAizo5DTOb8HIJPM2CBOFXutRFqt4-ru5R7uWwYI0lmaZtfcFtNLKmxyfRUMowtS55FGJjvNqBqeP62OEauMpZkm3ahZD0ztB1Izupgk32347q.png)
  
  #### Data Visualizations
  
  Data visualizations are diagrams that represent data in visual form. Like tables, charts, and graphs.
  
  These diagrams help users understand the data. And its implications.
  
  For example, this chart summarizes some findings from our [State of Search 2023 report](https://www.semrush.com/blog/state-of-search-2023/):
  
  ![Average click through rates for organic results compared for desktop and mobile devices for top ten positions.](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/b9/2a/b92a64720273c21871be18dc423d9afd/b6d91f54e2c912f0d6d456ffe5cea590/AD_4nXfTz3rM2_xz4beAsfnimV9zXlCtKVDwkryLE2t0dO8qcYJ1rntDIbwB919FEri5HZ4YMPehHQkW6OJ3SUDZj1z7ymJOyfCN9T8kqNHcSzg7CP5Txb0gqX1Xexgytj6weLkYGXq0LJQJZlNehD0uc8Ai-dBK.png)
  
  This format makes it far easier for readers to digest lots of information. And compare the different figures.
  
  ### 6\. Add Block Quotes
  
  Block quotes are portions of text formatted as quotes on the page. They tend to have a special design, which adds visual interest.
  
  Consider using block quote formatting if you’re adding expert quotes to your blog post.
  
  Just like this Setup blog post has done:
  
  ![Block quote by Ryan Murrin highlighted in Setup blog post.](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/ba/79/ba79aa310d373209b88347598a56a5aa/bbb9ae4aa489759950211f4593210d6e/AD_4nXd5C0emykqS5zmijWglQq4CzkimiVNbjfoaPbxNcorcQUe7yAxnm6ygOyHQrm3Ms3ZrWCEKFxm4RDNR2WWuyfvLnO61uWaVrzDeMUdtCP_rnbB0n4w6C23Fj2PpoOFn6Hf9qCyJYdt0RAkYzROURhMe5hRs.png)
  
  Many CMSs can help with block quote formatting.
  
  If you’re formatting your post in WordPress’s editor, highlight the text you want to turn into a block quote. Then, click the paragraph icon (¶) in the block toolbar and select “ **Quote**.”
  
  ![WordPress toolbar showing option to transform paragraph text to quote.](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/d1/c6/d1c6c0030a6712fcf1447e22a9e8b609/21917183ef78b75804888ed416722561/AD_4nXebmCLFxYwW6ebqcF5aT0p-apk3S9WQinnb2fQhQ0M9cK0DLQBFileh6cgl1Kur8NFFETGNYFXLxoTA-wPrhFb7x2QRTZcilxNKE9LbfE6iWcO76mB0xXG0PcOX3cw122IBBvQljvdYpO5vVzPILikIO6M8.png)
  
  ### 7\. Use Call-to-Action Buttons and Banners
  
  Format your CTAs as buttons and banners. These grab more attention than plain CTA text.
  
  For example, here’s a banner from our content marketing strategy guide:
  
  ![CTA banner for One2Target tool in body content of Semrush blog post.](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/87/29/872971fb352f1c94ac7ac1108bc72635/751e2d818661632c0063af2ddb7144e5/AD_4nXda8opu-tUloLOpSgBHzYxwz3f62Ufb8tIstvtvt3VilgqdGIfdenkhKqAOkqBtprtNHk6LvUX5oK-mjsR3l4eP6Uo_ZS9bLVEXS51az8thJ9o9-R_UI0YCtTNODZL1i66p3vcFknGLX1_KbEOUeclg3Fbc.png)
  
  We could have simply typed our CTA out in plain text. But it wouldn’t have been as obvious. Or as compelling to click.
  
  Your CMS may have a built-in feature for creating buttons.
  
  To add buttons to a WordPress post, open the post in the editor. Type “/” on your keyboard to display the block toolbar, and then select “ **Buttons**.”
  
  Doing this will add a button to your post.
  
  Fill it out with your CTA text. Next, click the text and then click the link icon to provide your CTA’s URL.
  
  ![CTA button in WordPress editor with add url option selected and highlighted.](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/07/e9/07e991c51492ba87fb6ee0574a9bf225/f09404bb78f1487a151c84293cdcb7de/AD_4nXeAT9ECRDRQbLImltec5d1KxnM2t2EDvZ7Nh5XFiusorfQCLLaPBijRKJkBYzGSC87te-UcArsqZQCYLLyI6JqiExSPGXndXOCPM_adOdJ_1zdrJFklKUttPMn5k-SpOQ9zxVWchtTOFc-GU2iJmeEXlBo.png)
  
  Finally, use the right sidebar settings to customize your button’s design.
  
  To add a banner, create it as an image in a graphic design app like [Canva](https://www.canva.com/). Then, embed the banner into your post and link it to your CTA’s destination page.
  
  ## Examples of Common Blog Post Types for Inspiration
  
  Here, we’ll analyze the formatting of some common blog post types.
  
  ### Listicle Posts
  
  Listicles are articles with the main content in list form. Listicle writers tend to format each list item as an H2 heading.
  
  They may also number each heading. To help users monitor their progress through the list.
  
  Just like this 10-tip listicle for saving water by WWF:
  
  ![Top ten water saving tips post by wwf](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/95/f1/95f16a74872a9f5c25ad1808e14125a5/71b840d53bccd5ce28b6f51a9f9a608e/AD_4nXdKwqc4HcM0wVYX9JCg6eSFksSQ1nhxZVqA47p7k7Q2gbfNMnwAK8XRWkg4QAk5AR2Xsngd5p2aet45_Y162nE7LTg9kgu8gBjk3aaZEV9BxWtLqnxk6sa8tB40sCvdRZwLGtSpdKVgTUIm7pOs.jpeg)
  
  Check out our [blog post templates](https://www.semrush.com/blog/blog-post-templates/) for a listicle blog post format template (and more).
  
  ### How-To Articles
  
  How-to articles provide information on how to do something. Writers usually present the instructions as numbered headings or lists. So readers know the order in which they should follow them.
  
  The article may also include supporting visuals to clarify the steps.
  
  Ties.com’s article on tying the Windsor knot is a good example. It starts with a video that walks users through the process:
  
  ![How to tie a Windsor knot blog post with embedded YouTube video.](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/41/59/41591b94c1d7c20b13be38e1fbe02222/042f5dde274cf6ed8b5786c0a6f40604/AD_4nXf8LcFs85ryrnxwioyvb42HwzfmsKZrhFpsiWOpT61OTgvM06O13pi6Y5GxXUfMVOAwLULZbLJx_XzTey1bfQxpFZhhdrxTXV9FHrshFZIlDvZoKIUtI0xB9Vqtv-nGySIq4_aSZgAE9vzUKPf3kaghNQjR.png)
  
  It then provides a list of step-by-step instructions. With images to illustrate.
  
  ![Image and text instructions showing how to tie a Windsor knot.](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/7a/01/7a017b30eef1478a1648d7684c2c8a02/6d32a6d8795072af3aa2832880bbbe8f/AD_4nXcrXS4pPy_wdso7VToe_po-0OTIXwO1bAVR-81pe2bYb7af5WQMqC1exNdKRfvyR4JId2ZcmgLNQiDZzH9R_g1TEgctDd1x1mZKYCSPHPNrbFRTB-iuZWW3FZfgCWkRQe9vJvuInxcFw1bl3vDCDac1G5Lo.png)
  
  Grab a how-to article template from our collection of [blog post templates](https://www.semrush.com/blog/blog-post-templates/).
  
  ### Review Articles
  
  Review articles assess the qualities of a product or service.
  
  To help readers follow the discussion, they may use formatting elements like:
  
  - Headings for each review criterion
  - Lists of the product or service’s features, pros, and cons
  - Images and videos showing the product or service in action
  - CTA buttons and banners that readers can click to buy the product or sign up for the service
  
  For example, Jeroen Van Nieuwenhove’s review article on the DJI Mavic 3 Pro drone features some photos he captured using the drone. And photos of the drone itself.
  
  ![Three images clicked using DJI Mavic in review blog post.](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/b9/00/b9006dbf393caa30513cec98b8006214/18e22084287b4310529351609b127464/AD_4nXduRI-zLjUGGQA4wgdaLBRv-ZdjTWQ5Obk8rQQN325KY15Tqqjrd9UCkcMubz81s9TeAIDbE-3MTwNeezbPHKFw3WZRJoVj36oOJ8hCTk1z2OoXNMb-bmKXxRUuymbFEi-1QwYBH4HnkHuFU8cObMKZzbNV.jpeg)
  
  The article also concisely covers the drone’s pros and cons as unordered lists.
  
  Plus, these lists are in side-by-side colored boxes. Which makes them stand out.
  
  ![Pros and cons listed together in blog post.](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/a3/66/a36667b62d4a2752472e137164ed187c/1aab19b62df970c53b1f42c1b45db116/AD_4nXeMgolQnZ5byt7DpmLQHlyaKvx0B1y-r0ZKTL4hug2d8oX3MEr9FjTud-2i53mb-2MiP_jdoKOn1sj7-S89p-KRtykA8iNb_IBzmkhf6jjxlJE8mVDrEAGreoycVlCsgbT8az54vsqNAsnXvXURBreikuY4.png)
  
  ### Comparison Posts
  
  Comparison posts evaluate two or more products or services against each other.
  
  They commonly include data visualizations. To help readers compare features at a glance.
  
  For example, Versus uses a radar chart to show how two earphone models compare on key criteria:
  
  ![Radar chart comparing different metrics for two earphone models on Versus' website.](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/e9/3d/e93d8fdc6570a9ef0421ce37c1d07e32/715e9d606386929333617130342f5d58/AD_4nXdjaEykFtthBWPGeFnf82YtD3PxIMZtbvsektH287FLKP4p9U4yZbhguN4HHIEiBIE32UtKS3wd7ygZZEHO85ErQrk8dTqopj1p3GUeaX_L0zCqRU_6wWA9r37apSrAdXIkMknhjVPhsjQKdtLm8VoUoNjj.png)
  
  And this table on Elegant Themes’s post makes it easy to compare the Wix website platform against WordPress:
  
  ![Elegant Themes blog post format with comparison table in conclusion of post.](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/d2/78/d278fdadcc87a48394a43b4bd3f3c4d0/2ec8bfbcdcae577f43c9231f2c567802/AD_4nXccIwso66yPhUvco_VW3pThYb929Caoz2A5YRj_Z7J1YxxUjbrXtrsNwbBprAX50dw18tNYChG-LgGaCTJ46Blk0sovbapCu_YPiTHhWyP7pPBxY_8TIcwlRpjXLm4s0CoUfyc5IhbZmOAtmp_-EzTc4raP.png)
  
  ### Expert Guides
  
  Expert guides are in-depth informational pieces on a subject. Their typical formatting elements include:
  
  - Headings for each topic
  - A table of contents showing the guide’s topics
  - Visuals to illustrate concepts
  - Lists of bite-sized information
  - Block quotes for expert opinions and/or soundbites
  
  For instance, MassChallenge’s seven-step guide to starting a tech company presents each step as a numbered heading:
  
  ![7 steps to build a successful tech company heading followed by numbered heading.](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/b9/1b/b91b65139ea2cd5025d8dcddad89898f/492f2579bb99bcdd99fe03edf9f4b8f8/AD_4nXdusBBz-PHdk5Tv9YwRpC9PcrL6tl26YqbCQQ6WbdT-iSWWy0uzNl-H4KQRYRVN_wOyBb4mzZ7UKsrgPXg7KHimyODLcl7yJPg6Q3zEuqf23Uv-dULRvDxzQVZyYAcwh41MUIvFrlIpva2rEGjpHvxE2dL2.png)
  
  It includes charts for visualizing data:
  
  ![Numbered heading followed by chart visualizing data.](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/cf/46/cf46c844c285a79c424465373e2c94a0/6015576b5cd2af022a090494bf0c3b0c/AD_4nXdvoKBjfXt_RL1VTkku2tClWsmC-v-rCgkBI8LnU-oZGrrBytJ3mesXFYLllZnTnjA8OfKKW6R9TtzBAwJqzAxPbrYBhAj5f_0vuoi_oUAHbAButAUF0K4axZuTNiP6awnuqIgAYezlYqdQd2fof9ztccBA.png)
  
  And the guide displays certain information as succinct lists:
  
  ![Unordered list of types of MVP.](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/f0/f1/f0f12f7c4ea73504cffe20469e72ea13/04979db5470510f3531ad1d01f9a50ee/AD_4nXcdnNYLpaR8SzVH6OrhX8OYWNoTNkVd-1e_zlGm3H3Ge8WyUeXttwFAseX20pXQ4vCK2LHJN1mXEIvbRohlSNt1LAWJCe8GFFtzfl8arkBrxqDsGedivA-nyj4lVjY8rArRjf0ac9tExPoTt-7aYqoBFUw.png)
  
  It also prominently features quotes from tech leaders in block quotes.
  
  ![In content quote by tech leader.](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/aa/10/aa10de988adbb204673a7529a52a6a77/d769f89b7a8185133e2d730db98a6804/AD_4nXdgHKf0QdT9d1odKtCTdXKqor9XldnfLCmPqSY6f0ri8dkxWK_gPGNiAqSXOltj2-GG-t_77aF_qUG9UvT9ZwaZ9mVrPcRpMFsuWlb_NwTpeNTBEcq-aN3ltRysx0xLce8M7Srz2MQHKlvhhW2WUNGk4LX9.png)
  
