  # Blog Post Examples and Best Practices to Inspire Your Writing
  
  Author: [Sydney Go](https://www.semrush.com/blog/user/sydney-go/)
  
  18 min read
  
  March 6, 2024
  
  Contributor: [Bartłomiej Barcik](https://www.semrush.com/blog/user/207807681/)
  
  Table of contents
  
  ## What Is a Blog Post?
  
  A blog post is a piece of writing typically published on a website's blog that presents information, opinions, experiences, or insights on a particular topic. Blog posts vary in length. And can include text, images, or videos, depending on the topic.
  
  For instance, travel blogs are often rich in visuals. Showcasing the beauty or uniqueness of the places described.
  
  Like this blog post from travel blog [Nomadic Matt](https://www.nomadicmatt.com/travel-blogs/where-to-stay-brisbane/):
  
  ![Nomadic Matt's blog post titled "Where to stay in Brisbane: The best neighborhoods for your visit"](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/1e/ee/1eee89701c9d9243a08d180947cbcbdd/78e3afa881dccfdd69969975f35f7617/travel-blog-post-example.jpg)
  
  Business blog posts tend to be text-heavy. Focusing on data, expert interviews, industry news, statistics, and other helpful insights.
  
  Like this blog post on [Entrepreneur](https://www.entrepreneur.com/growing-a-business/ai-is-changing-how-we-look-at-jobs-heres-how-to-prepare/467380):
  
  ![Entrepreneur's article on how AI is changing the way we look at job skills](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/46/7f/467f47c9a33c2a5fd62c2ef823609bde/6b07a82c8a0d0071f11d55bc56ab4f46/tIHJtjjyDw7L5c8m65swOntAJQVFQC8URCRLqiGk4hZUb_apDa9BtcQ8G74RqBUWkL8hqi5nEWIzJXeuAwzwzi3EGS_3C-_2RPo65uqE_yBX_mOY5OS-7sN3T6Pgbwb1fh8XWZXYx9CShIzLx2CyGoY.png)
  
  ### What Is a Blog?
  
  A blog, or weblog, is a regularly updated website (or page on a website) that features blog posts on various topics. The content is usually written in a conversational style, addressing the reader directly.
  
  ## How Does Blogging Benefit Your Business?
  
  Blogging has many potential benefits. Here, we look at the top advantages of creating blog posts for your business.
  
  ### Builds Authority and Trust
  
  Blogging can be a powerful tool if you’re looking to establish authority in your industry.
  
  By consistently creating valuable and informative content, you can demonstrate expertise. And engage with your audience in meaningful ways.
  
  Here's how blogging helps build authority:
  
  - **Showcases expertise**: Blog posts that tackle industry issues, explain complex concepts, or provide how-to guides showcase your depth of knowledge. This helps position you as a thought leader in your industry.
  - **Improves SEO**: Well-crafted blog posts that incorporate relevant keywords can improve a website's [search engine rankings](https://www.semrush.com/blog/seo-ranking/). Higher visibility in search results can lead to increased website traffic. And leads.
  - **Builds trust**: By providing valuable content without a hard sell, businesses can build trust with their audience
  
  ### Gives You Full Control
  
  With a blog, you have full control over the content you publish. Including the length, format, and topics you cover.
  
  Blogging platforms like Medium and social media sites like Facebook can remove content at any time. And for any reason.
  
  This may happen if what you write goes against their guidelines, someone (such as a competitor) reports your posts, or the platform goes out of business.
  
  ### Builds Internal Links
  
  Another advantage of blogging is that it lets you build [internal links](https://www.semrush.com/blog/internal-links/), which can improve website navigation. Internal links connect various pages of your website, guiding customers through relevant content and product pages.
  
  A streamlined path makes it easier for customers to find and explore your products and other pages.
  
  ![An internal link from one page on your website (left) to another page with relevant content (right)](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/7a/d9/7ad902d5d46fc026ffa8099bb45dc610/bbc863ee9a6b3a2fe436b9dcbbf545d2/blog-post-link-to-relevant-content.png)
  
  Let's say you run an online store selling dietary supplements. You write about the benefits of protein on your blog. And link to product pages selling protein powder, protein bars, or other related products.
  
  If your blog post is relevant and engaging, readers might click those links. And purchase the products you mentioned.
  
  ### Improves Traffic and Visibility
  
  Incorporating [SEO best practices](https://www.semrush.com/blog/seo-best-practices/) into your content may lead to higher rankings, resulting in more traffic and exposure.
  
  For example, optimizing each blog post for specific keywords, such as "whey protein powder" or "vegan protein bars," can help you get more targeted organic traffic. Keywords are search terms used by consumers to find information or products online.
  
  Additionally, readers may share your blog posts on social media. Which can further boost website traffic and brand awareness.
  
  ### Increases Backlinks
  
  Blog posts are a great way to [build backlinks](https://www.semrush.com/blog/what-are-backlinks/) for your website or blog. Backlinks are incoming links from one website to another, acting as votes of confidence that help signal your site's authority to search engines.
  
  High-quality backlinks can help boost your search engine rankings. And lead to more traffic.
  
  The more traffic you get, the likelier your target audience is to discover your brand and products. Some may become paying customers. And help spread the word about your business.
  
  ### Lets You Target Users in All Funnel Stages
  
  Blogging lets you create content for each stage of the [marketing funnel](https://www.semrush.com/blog/marketing-funnel/). Which can help you attract, convert, and retain customers.
  
  Here’s a quick look at how to apply the marketing funnel to blog content:
  
  - **Top of the funnel (ToFu)**: Create how-to posts, listicles, infographics, and other types of content for new audiences. These people are just discovering your blog, products, or services. The goal is to build awareness of the problem you can solve.
  - **Middle of the funnel (MoFu)**: Produce longer, more in-depth content, such as ultimate guides, case studies, and comparison posts, for readers who are already familiar with your business. At this point, you’ll want to generate interest in your offerings.
  - **Bottom of the funnel (BoFu)**: Go into detail about the products or services you promote on your blog with detailed reviews and product demos. Your readers are ready to take the desired action (e.g., book a consultation)—they just need an extra push.
  
  ![A visual of a simple conversion funnel, with tofu, mofu, and bofu sections](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/79/d6/79d6bd308dc7882269ad13fb819cb268/0fffd398ed95ca12f3f87388361fd445/simple-conversion-funnel-tofu-mofu-bofu.png)
  
  _**Further reading**_ _:_ [_ToFu, MoFu, BoFu: A Practical Guide to the Conversion Funnel_](https://www.semrush.com/blog/tofu-mofu-bofu-a-practical-guide-to-the-conversion-funnel/)
  
  ## 6 Effective Blog Post Formats
  
  There’s more than one way to format blog posts, depending on where your target audience is in the funnel. And your goals for the content.
  
  With that in mind, let's see some of the most common types of blog posts.
  
  ### 1\. Listicles
  
  Listicles are articles or blog posts organized in list format.
  
  For example, a blog post titled “Top 10 Movies to Watch This Weekend” or “10 Must-Have Kitchen Appliances Every Home Needs” would be considered a listicle.
  
  Use listicles to break complex topics into smaller, more manageable chunks. And share tips, strategies, products, or ideas.
  
  For instance, Healthline uses this format to cover complex topics in a clear and engaging manner.
  
  Below, you can see a [listicle blog post](https://www.healthline.com/nutrition/27-health-and-nutrition-tips) about health and nutrition, broken down into 27 tips.
  
  ![Healthline's listicle blog post about health and nutrition, broken down into 27 tips](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/ea/e8/eae8f95580541f2174cc475b6ecba342/dac035152d4153215170dc27f59c9fb2/iaxX5nCsZMOboyN6WC9BPdxOIgz4fET9zo0tS384xGG5TT5w9xsThaslITUwb7fh4TMvxDT7dr4PKw2log7dAqUtvF4cF6kTqWbuCRxoIOoEKnHK9uZyEiz5k7gjl7Wbdnl9F_yoTmlpFVBGOT1pO_k.png)
  
  Each tip is numbered and covers one idea, such as "Don't fear coffee” and "Eat fatty fish.”
  
  ![Healthline's listicle tips on "Don't fear coffee” and "Eat fatty fish"](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/5f/b6/5fb68ebe537dd64a66c0ba73dca879f6/88c451cbf54fe87bfbff5580aa641688/_uYR9a56aN3sxFptux7sg50jFCbuCqZ5Qg1uCrg_Dg4IQ0KIOvp6HxXGyJFXWA3zsNFUhBAitayDLCBvJkYDuZVr1hdjcknaRoCZkJ2WaSu1pYZ1lvMialF1bPmLRUDhS9pytZccBt12-5frbD9o7nc.png)
  
  Listicles are easy to read and highly shareable. Which can help you reach a wider audience. As a result, they tend to [attract more traffic and links](https://mailchimp.com/resources/listicles/), increasing your visibility online.
  
  ### 2\. "How-To" Blog Posts
  
  How-to content provides actionable insights that help readers grasp complex concepts or learn something new. It may also answer common questions on a given topic or introduce new concepts.
  
  For example, the following [Shopify blog post](https://www.shopify.com/blog/start-online-store) shows readers how to start an online store.
  
  ![Shopify's blog post on how to start an online store](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/6d/7f/6d7fd75f472991ca8dd9ea65b509fe93/138416b97511ae0ee1e5c0c5957085d8/how-to-blog-post-example.png)
  
  The article consists of 10 steps that guide users through the process. From choosing a target audience to promoting their store.
  
  [Apartment Therapy](https://www.apartmenttherapy.com/how-to-clean-a-humidifier-using-only-vinegar-37326936) published a short how-to post on how to clean a humidifier using only vinegar.
  
  ![Apartment Therapy's blog post on how to clean a humidifier using only vinegar](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/65/75/6575eb8b58d8cd354cbac53d21645cc0/4268046861a2d5f89df312aff6f557d9/short-how-to-blog-post-example.jpg)
  
  The content is broken down into five actionable steps. And includes relevant images.
  
  Generally, how-to blog posts provide practical solutions. They're more hands-on compared to a case study, product review, or news article.
  
  If readers find your content useful, they'll likely want more from you. This means they could browse your blog for further insights, join your email list, or follow your blog on social media.
  
  ### 3\. Checklists and Cheat Sheets
  
  Checklists and cheat sheets are an effective way to summarize information. While offering practical advice or solutions.
  
  This type of content can also highlight key points or takeaways related to a broader topic. At the same time, it makes it easier to organize information, ideas, or concepts in a structured way.
  
  For example, lifestyle blogger Joanna Goddard [wrote a blog post](https://cupofjo.com/2023/05/22/a-very-low-key-summer-checklist-2/) called "A Very Low-Key Summer Checklist." The article includes 10 fun, creative ideas for a memorable summer.
  
  ![Joanna Goddard's blog post titled "A Very Low-Key Summer Checklist"](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/92/cd/92cd7063ef0d610d6928939e18a6e733/5cf7e371c9e69e392c81dc4e56e94b83/checklist-blog-post-example.jpg)
  
  Use checklists to present complex information in a simplified manner.
  
  For instance, [Net Solutions](https://www.netsolutions.com/insights/7-step-mobile-app-development-checklist/) published a seven-step mobile app development checklist. This topic is broad and complex. But the article breaks it down into easy-to-follow steps.
  
  ![Net Solutions's article on seven-step mobile app development checklist](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/68/08/6808887738892aeca55c85093b062d64/a1d342be9eea7920a4652d5a4361e9e8/Ph3DVvEAljuLUNPXN4MOfsNcTDAchCWTSY42vGSL5hG070GI2d0fJeEr7EYXbTXZSqNDni_26CLjHjlHZmrutwkWMtggbbxhQInL27_S2eYq0UkKp1C0qSt4wGQXTeiiPGqwc1JVbNsr7RnirVsSiG8.png)
  
  Just like listicles, checklists are user-friendly and highly shareable, allowing blog readers to grasp the main points quickly.
  
  As a result, they can drive engagement. And help you get your message across more clearly.
  
  ### 4\. Ultimate Guides
  
  Ultimate guides cover a topic in depth. These blog posts are often used as [pillar content](https://www.semrush.com/blog/pillar-page/), serving as the foundation for other articles and resources on a website.
  
  Ultimate guides are longer and more detailed than informational and how-to articles. But shorter than an ebook. They usually include lists, visuals, and multiple headings that make the content easier to digest.
  
  An example is our ["Ultimate Guide to Content Marketing Strategy](https://www.semrush.com/blog/content-marketing-strategy-guide/)."
  
  It begins with a definition of content marketing, explains why it's important, and then describes the steps involved in creating a strategy.
  
  ![Semrush's blog titled "Ultimate Guide to Content Marketing Strategy"](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/75/a0/75a046cba14c2dd4aed949058f7cdb1b/1ae7b018675d84de0356fc2802389fdf/LzsIk4Pd7DJqYMDq8wR_-MvrW5mqaPfPyZUWlI6v84FA0XwG1GqtFcR40cEJ3F7z_wjYER428VMdLsLjBL601E5sL7hy-DvGps7SISemyxSkLd-Jw7ZFgokcfTRZdoDYpvlEjo1RmBNYWJ5skCf-obs.png)
  
  It also includes screenshots, images, real-world examples, and other resources on the topic.
  
  ![An example including a screenshot from Sermush's "Ultimate Guide to Content Marketing Strategy" blog post](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/65/85/658593a592fd326379f98da869d2b276/d852f3de7c80b380525e1af2d64d080d/vLoR1EYNhI8Y4pGKN4Dw0vtsw0oqWGDGTDpOhY0VGLXbNkdUEEHuyhzuxQrvflR9ahnV-LNJTtFLnw1rdv8BDskWWBHDmCqXOqPP2o8PApns83AFTdm2032JHogzK_0dVpw5bY7RengLIxP0lALLrCk.png)
  
  Another example of an ultimate guide is the blog [Under30Experiences](https://www.under30experiences.com/blog/solo-travel-guide). Which features a guide to traveling alone.
  
  ![Under30Experiences' solo travel guide](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/38/c9/38c91ace52d5c715c0b0fe399c810871/f5547c629ac8bb74468e6abf4b64151f/eYhLRsuQ_xoL6W35rwdRJFxOK9GJy4M1AZiH45Hu8thNnNImYkNFTVud1QTxfhasi3EYlakY-ipDqV7m2obctr1hmzD3FnDlmCsF5Q_nsjrh7WCVDOvI8dMZ88Q1TSF8Zrc-pMmLcpHAaQQHU0SAhjA.png)
  
  The blog post offers expert tips on how to plan your trip, stay safe, save money, and more.
  
  This type of long-form content works best for broad or complex topics. If done right, it may increase blog traffic and brand authority.
  
  Plus, it allows you to position yourself as an industry expert. And build credibility for your business.
  
  ### 5\. Reviews
  
  Reviews revolve around the products or services you offer or have used. They should be relevant to your audience.
  
  For example, if you have a blog about beauty and fashion, write about skincare products, makeup accessories, or clothing items.
  
  See this example from [Artistry Beauty](https://www.artistrybeautyblog.com/the-ordinary-hyaluronic-acid-review/), which features a review of The Ordinary’s hyaluronic acid product:
  
  ![Artistry Beauty's review of The Ordinary’s hyaluronic acid product](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/54/fe/54fe168a5206c8a61c36c5e722ec5ec3/48674e0e66e769ddbf95b817c26775ea/dIE1VcuXPeea3E-QOoVXuXd0ZtDdQf4mi2CPrDUNMbH9Dk0BAd9p-GITfqPOJHeIwxNnP9zbao2Bq6HQTUVueBaSl0GOHlHNOo7E47_06bjImOaPg3v6ICmHWXKijGGxaUdpkDVSwsVWBzUX9PxCIls.png)
  
  A business blog might feature reviews of newly launched apps, software programs, or books.
  
  As illustrated below:
  
  ![An article titles "8 Reasons I Love Using FreshBooks To Run My Blogging Business"](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/e3/c0/e3c04688903dd30377e5aff534442475/570ff6941db8f618dea1efb7d0ab20a8/l2pGJ_EXSbfbh5OenXGqF2gxAwoGS3e-BMmSFcZEWbOuv7WXaU8O2UQl4-PYcFZ9fvq3EHinIE-eBDYdKOqCT1W8bYZFNi9mRZ29nyzajP6EScXouBR0wnzTCPklPhXIBYroOzWS0kS72621ScVi2yU.png)
  
  If you sell a product or service, you may review other products or services that complement yours. For instance, a personal trainer could write about their experience with a particular protein brand or fitness center.
  
  With this type of content, you provide value to your audience by introducing them to products and services they may need or want.
  
  It's also an opportunity to target and rank for new keywords. Which can make your blog more discoverable in online searches.
  
  Your reviews may contain [affiliate links](https://www.semrush.com/blog/how-do-affiliate-programs-work/) to Amazon, ClickBank, or similar platforms. Affiliate links allow you to generate revenue every time someone purchases a product through your link.
  
  Just make sure you add a disclaimer ( [it’s a legal requirement](https://www.ftc.gov/business-guidance/resources/ftcs-endorsement-guides-what-people-are-asking)) to inform readers about your relationship with the seller.
  
  As shown below:
  
  ![A disclaimer about affiliate links on a blog page](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/9b/3c/9b3caeea7f934e1672f84cf77d45b31b/a3d68853f7cfb775a68b2b5a46bede34/NNOw0pO0HKEP7TA3MURyYAAGGlFQ6fMdiy58DMFV-vMfLY5dqsGj-IU5E5zQIRTE7SQicFrkO6JvMtonRAUqlxoV1OzcsSPhsg_SBSsqZR-hqWTRYTc87308XT6p3AmlQB6SzbaU9v4M9__ZhI7awIE.png)
  
  ### 6\. Comparisons
  
  This type of content is similar to review-style posts. But you'll compare two or more products.
  
  The goal here is to highlight the similarities and differences between those products. As well as their distinct pros and cons.
  
  Comparison guides can help your readers assess their options. And make an informed product decision. Plus, you may use them to show potential customers how your product or service measures against others.
  
  For example, this [blog post from Elegant Themes](https://www.elegantthemes.com/blog/resources/aweber-vs-mailchimp-which-is-better-suited-for-building-your-list) features a detailed comparison of AWeber and MailChimp:
  
  ![Elegant Themes's blog post comparing AWeber and MailChimp](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/b2/90/b2903a4ee5831b0a919ffa8fbea7f2f5/4fd7beb35c579209bbe881a91179ec2d/aL6X-rumNWFSY0zheO8Q4-2c5nnPC0orP7ztUNwiZVllatOTC6xwmL2GmubPhImrX28_mpQN2_SEShygPi4eOAqez3lU4llRMBzFiGZFAWfXm5Lvnqy_GWp0nYl5Zvxgzl2qrBd0hvHPC1tx1vc4p-c.png)
  
  It covers key features, usability, performance, and pricing options, among other aspects.
  
  This format works for blogs in other niches, too.
  
  For instance, [lifestyle blogger Cassie Sethna](https://cassiesethna.com/review-dyson-airwrap-vs-revlon-styler/) wrote about the Dyson Airwrap versus the Revlon Styler. After testing both products, she published a short post about their pros and cons:
  
  ![Cassie Sethna's comparision of Dyson Airwrap versus the Revlon Styler](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/16/c3/16c3535b3ab082b63f193b23191e231b/781062b1a0e8b5ec5cb27ace3e2730fb/EvkuLTQmTbGU2oi8vUC9spXPRoYQfVRmRi03ESruZhVx4RhNcl48bqQFsCWbjpfifpXGJRdnBvKpIFVSzUJgW7PJXnwYeNTY692wSwUi1HGMzY6nMdQiuPVAMKhg4lTjk6mRvCTRkjltX7Tqa3tOy5o.png)
  
