  ## Blog Post Basics for Writers
  
  Crafting engaging blog posts takes practice and planning. Follow these basics to get started.
  
  ### Research Relevant Blog Post Topics
  
  Most blogs cover a wide array of topics within specific categories. Like beauty, fitness, or tech. The challenge lies in finding interesting, relevant topics without repeating yourself.
  
  One solution is to usethe [Topic Research tool](https://www.semrush.com/topic-research/) to generate blog post ideas.
  
  First, log in to your Semrush account. Click " **Topic Research**" under " **Content Marketing**" from the left-side navigation menu.
  
  Next, enter a broad topic into the search bar. Like strength training.
  
  Type your term into the designated field. And choose your preferred country and language.
  
  When you're done, click " **Get content ideas**."
  
  ![Topic Research tool](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/ec/49/ec49265f27e0112d609f97b4c0b27938/3d12e225eb30192a649c275bb7e69ac1/SxeFKS4FNgQmF-BUtC4fm3_w5ibY6G1Z4RBIMeqgyVWw-4fMT-2shyizdX4ZASfzsk4W5VZQbH8w8ZIcvAwrXzI9zARGXwdJIVfx0a80RFYMUDYapqTxnpB8GJqU9xnG3jUSfkNmC8OquTz0yZ7dNhg.png)
  
  Next, you’ll see a list of blog topics.
  
  !["Content Ideas" dashboard for ·strength training" in Topic Research tool](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/8f/c0/8fc071920f0204b3a220358b4cb854dc/53061226725739445238fd705d1ed187/PF2kFGB1u1TDJprl6LcCitErLvG0Co9pIPan62aoc-PBneWz--vCoKYJTxSw_R2-Nd_JU5fYRD8lVEO--_Hp3wHl3Xobo3VRWWoqv_zxs_T3j74zrpy76nj7ItNn3XU-CofRbbZZrLWJMVR1lRe42SE.png)
  
  The tool organizes topics by category. Select the category you're interested in and click " **Show more**" to see all the content ideas under that category.
  
  For example, if you click "Lifting Weights," you'll get multiple headlines and questions to address in your blog post.
  
  ![Headlines, and questions related to "Lifting Weights" in Topic Research tool](https://static.semrush.com/blog/uploads/media/03/2b/032b6b97ca1b225c9fbb17dc42dab141/220f9c0f21d05775c3cc82ae5ed1d7a9/7_77viAs82aGmwSi1bj6EyDWDEiz1hoIy-KQVrU7ci10J2kwOTQd233Dz25-8DRVdP7FDtzlyYNz8Gc98Q3Plq3xqe0Onuws2MEL3_KdWvpiBCKGOguwaXaotVbTO_N-KbN9wmdA_ll7Mqka5UBOces.png)
  
  Alternatively, use Quora, Reddit, X (formerly known as Twitter), or Google Trends to explore content ideas.
  
  Enter your topic in the search bar to see what’s trending. And what people want to know about that topic.
  
